//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15;
  wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3, sum4, sum5, sum6, sum7, sum8, sum9, sum10, sum11, sum12, sum13, sum14, sum15;
  
  full_adder_16 FA1(sum1, c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_16 FA2(sum2, c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_16 FA3(sum3, c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_16 FA4(sum4, c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_16 FA5(sum5, c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_16 FA6(sum6, c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_16 FA7(sum7, c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_16 FA8(sum8, c8, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
  full_adder_16 FA9(sum9, c9, in1[8], in2[8], c8);
  full_adder_16 FA10(sum10, c10, in1[9], in2[9], c9);
  full_adder_16 FA11(sum11, c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
  full_adder_16 FA12(sum12, c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);
  full_adder_16 FA13(sum13, c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);
  full_adder_16 FA14(sum14, c14, in1[13], in2[13], c13);
  full_adder_16 FA15(sum15, c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
  
  full_adder_16 FA16(sum, cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15;
  wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3, sum4, sum5, sum6, sum7, sum8, sum9, sum10, sum11, sum12, sum13, sum14, sum15;
  
  full_adder_16 FA1(sum1, c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_16 FA2(sum2, c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_16 FA3(sum3, c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_16 FA4(sum4, c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

  full_adder_16 FA9(sum9, c9, in1[8], in2[8], c8);

  full_adder_16 FA12(sum12, c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);

endmodule

module full_adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input in1, in2,
                      input cin);

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15;
  wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3, sum4, sum5, sum6, sum7, sum8, sum9, sum10, sum11, sum12, sum13, sum14, sum15;
  
  full_adder_16 FA1(sum1, c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_16 FA2(sum2, c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_16 FA3(sum3, c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_16 FA4(sum4, c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_16 FA5(sum5, c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);

  full_adder_16 FA7(sum7, c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_16 FA8(sum8, c8, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
  full_adder_16 FA9(sum9, c9, in1[8], in2[8], c8);
  full_adder_16 FA10(sum10, c10, in1[9], in2[9], c9);
  full_adder_16 FA11(sum11, c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
  full_adder_16 FA12(sum12, c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);
  full_adder_16 FA13(sum13, c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1,
                  input wire in2);
  xor(sum, in1, in2);
  and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

  full_adder_16 FA14(sum14, c14, in1, in2, c13);
  full_adder_16 FA15(sum15, cout, in1, in2, c14);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1,
                  input wire in2);
  xor(sum, in1, in2);
  and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    assign {cout, sum} = in1_temp + in2_temp + cin_temp;

endmodule

//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire cin;

    assign in2_temp = in2;

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15;
  wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3, sum4, sum5, sum6, sum7, sum8, sum9, sum10, sum11, sum12, sum13, sum14, sum15;
  
  full_adder_16 FA1(sum1, c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder_16 FA2(sum2, c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder_16 FA3(sum3, c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder_16 FA4(sum4, c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder_16 FA5(sum5, c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  full_adder_16 FA6(sum6, c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  full_adder_16 FA7(sum7, c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  full_adder_16 FA8(sum8, c8, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
  full_adder_16 FA9(sum9, c9, in1[8], in2[8], c8);

  full_adder_16 FA11(sum11, c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
  full_adder_16 FA12(sum12, c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1,
                  input wire in2);

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);
  wire a, b, c;
  xor(a, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, a, cin);
  and(b, a, cin);
  and(c, in1, in2);
  or(cout, b, c);
endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);

wire xor1, and1, and2;

xor(xor1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, xor1, cin);
and(and1, xor1, cin);
and(and2, in1, in2);
or(cout, and1, and2);

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 
  wire c1, c2, c3;
  full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);
  wire a, b, c;
  xor(a, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, a, cin);
  and(b, a, cin);
  and(c, in1, in2);
  or(cout, b, c);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    assign {cout, sum} = in1_temp + in2_temp + cin_temp;

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);


    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    assign {cout, sum} = in1_temp + in2_temp + cin_temp;

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum1[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum1[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum1[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
    full_adder_16 FA4(sum1[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3;

    full_adder_16 FA2(sum1[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);

    full_adder_16 FA15(sum1[14], c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
    full_adder_16 FA16(sum1[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);
endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum1, c1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(sum2, c2, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA3(sum3, c3, in1, in2);
    
    assign sum = sum1 ^ sum2 ^ sum3;
    assign cout = c1 ^ c2 ^ c3;
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum1[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum1[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum1[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum1, c1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(sum2, c2, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA3(sum3, c3, in1, in2);
    
    assign sum = sum1 ^ sum2 ^ sum3;
    assign cout = c1 ^ c2 ^ c3;
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);

    assign sum = in1 ^ in2;
    assign cout = in1 & in2;
endmodule

full_adder FA16(sum[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);

wire xor1, and1, and2;

xor(xor1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, xor1, cin);
and(and1, xor1, cin);
and(and2, in1, in2);
or(cout, and1, and2);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);

wire xor1, and1, and2;

xor(xor1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, xor1, cin);
and(and1, xor1, cin);
and(and2, in1, in2);
or(cout, and1, and2);

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

wire [15:0] sum_temp;
wire [15:0] in1_temp;
wire [15:0] in2_temp;

assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
assign in1_temp = in1;
assign in2_temp = in2;

assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
assign cout = sum_temp[16];

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    assign {cout, sum} = in1_temp + in2_temp + cin_temp;

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum1[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum1[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum1[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum1[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum1[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
    full_adder_16 FA4(sum1[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum1, c1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(sum2, c2, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA3(sum3, c3, in1, in2);
    
    assign sum = sum1 ^ sum2 ^ sum3;
    assign cout = c1 ^ c2 ^ c3;
endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum1, c1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(sum2, c2, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA3(sum3, c3, in1, in2);
    
    assign sum = sum1 ^ sum2 ^ sum3;
    assign cout = c1 ^ c2 ^ c3;
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);

    assign sum = in1 ^ in2;
    assign cout = in1 & in2;
endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);                                   
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);  
  
  wire [15:0] sum;
  wire cout;
  
  wire [15:0] in1;
  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;
  
  assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
  assign cout = (in1[15] == in2[15] && in1[15] == cin)? 1'b1 : 1'b0;
  
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

wire [15:0] sum_temp;
wire [15:0] in1_temp;
wire [15:0] in2_temp;

assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
assign in1_temp = in1;
assign in2_temp = in2;

assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
assign cout = sum_temp[16];

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 
  wire c1, c2, c3;
  full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  full_adder FA5(sum[4], c4, in1[4], in2[4], c3);
  full_adder FA6(sum[5], c5, in1[5], in2[5], c4);

  full_adder FA11(sum[10], c10, in1[10], in2[10], c9);
  full_adder FA12(sum[11], c11, in1[11], in2[11], c10);
  full_adder FA13(sum[12], c12, in1[12], in2[12], c11);
  full_adder FA14(sum[13], c13, in1[13], in2[13], c12);
  full_adder FA15(sum[14], c14, in1[14], in2[14], c13);
  full_adder FA16(sum[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c14);
endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);
  wire a, b, c;
  xor(a, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, a, cin);
  and(b, a, cin);
  and(c, in1, in2);
  or(cout, b, c);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

assign {cout, sum} = in1 + in2 + cin;

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
        wire [15:0] sum;
        wire cout;
        wire [15:0] in1;
        wire [15:0] in2;
        wire cin;
        
        full_adder_16 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
        full_adder_16 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);

                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);

        wire c2;
        wire c3;
        wire c4;
        wire c5;
        wire c6;
        wire c7;
        wire c8;
        wire c9;
        wire c10;
        wire c11;
        wire c12;
        wire c13;
        wire c14;
        wire c15;

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
        xor(sum, in1, in2);
        and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.

module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    assign {cout, sum} = in1_temp + in2_temp + cin_temp;

endmodule

//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.

                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    full_adder_16 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;

                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;

    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);
  wire a, b, c;
  xor(a, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, a, cin);
  and(b, a, cin);
  and(c, in1, in2);
  or(cout, b, c);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);                              
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;

    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);
  wire a, b, c;
  xor(a, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, a, cin);
  and(b, a, cin);
  and(c, in1, in2);
  or(cout, b, c);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);                              

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1_temp & in2_temp);
    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;
    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.

                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

module full_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1,
                  input wire in2,
                  input wire cin);

wire temp1;
wire temp2;
wire temp3;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(temp1,in1,in2);
and(temp2,in1,cin);
and(temp3,in2,cin);
or(cout,temp1,temp2,temp3);

endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
full_adder FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
full_adder FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
full_adder FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
full_adder FA8(sum[7], c8, in1[7], in2[7], c7);

full_adder FA10(sum[9], c10, in1[9], in2[9], c9);
full_adder FA11(sum[10], c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
full_adder FA12(sum[11], c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);
full_adder FA13(sum[12], c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);
full_adder FA14(sum[13], c14, in1[13], in2[13], c13);
full_adder FA15(sum[14], c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
full_adder FA16(sum[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);

wire xor1, and1, and2;

xor(xor1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, xor1, cin);
and(and1, xor1, cin);
and(and2, in1, in2);
or(cout, and1, and2);

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
 
  wire [15:0] sum;
  wire cout;
  wire [15:0] in1;
  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;
 
  adder_16_bit a1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
  adder_16_bit a2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
  adder_16_bit a3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
  adder_16_bit a4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
  adder_16_bit a5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
  adder_16_bit a6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
  adder_16_bit a7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
  adder_16_bit a8(sum[7], c8, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
  adder_16_bit a9(sum[8], c9, in1[8], in2[8], c8);
  adder_16_bit a10(sum[9], c10, in1[9], in2[9], c9);
  adder_16_bit a11(sum[10], c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
  adder_16_bit a12(sum[11], c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);
  adder_16_bit a13(sum[12], c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);
  adder_16_bit a14(sum[13], c14, in1[13], in2[13], c13);
  adder_16_bit a15(sum[14], c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
  adder_16_bit a16(sum[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);
 
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 

wire c1, c2, c3;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], cout, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);

wire x, y, z;

xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
and(x, in1, in2);
and(y, in1, cin);
and(z, in2, cin);
or(cout, x, y, z);

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);                              
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;

                      output cout,

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);
  wire a, b, c;
  xor(a, in1, in2);
  xor(sum, a, cin);
  and(b, a, cin);
  and(c, in1, in2);
  or(cout, b, c);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin); 

  wire [15:0] sum;
  wire cout;
  wire [15:0] in1;
  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;

  wire [15:0] sum_temp;
  wire cout_temp;
  wire [15:0] in1_temp;
  wire [15:0] in2_temp;
  wire cin_temp;

  assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
  assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

  assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
  assign cout = cout_temp;

  assign in1_temp = {1'b0, in1[15:1]};
  assign in2_temp = {1'b0, in2[15:1]};
  assign cin_temp = cin;

  always @(in1_temp or in2_temp or cin_temp)
  begin
    if (cin_temp == 1'b0)
    begin
      sum = sum_temp[15:0];
      cout = cout_temp;
    end
    else
    begin
      sum = 16'b0;
      cout = 1'b0;
    end
  end

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);                              
  wire [15:0] sum;
  wire cout;
  wire [15:0] in1;
  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;
  
  adder_16_bit a1(sum[15:0], cout, in1[15:0], in2[15:0], cin);
  adder_16_bit a2(sum[31:16], cout, in1[31:16], in2[31:16], cout);

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15;

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
full_adder FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
full_adder FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);

full_adder FA13(sum[12], c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);
full_adder FA14(sum[13], c14, in1[13], in2[13], c13);
full_adder FA15(sum[14], c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
full_adder FA16(sum[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);

wire xor1, and1, and2;

xor(xor1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, xor1, cin);
and(and1, xor1, cin);
and(and2, in1, in2);
or(cout, and1, and2);

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15;
  wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3, sum4, sum5, sum6, sum7, sum8, sum9, sum10, sum11, sum12, sum13, sum14, sum15;

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1,
                  input wire in2);

  and(cout, in1, in2);

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);


    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    assign {cout, sum} = in1_temp + in2_temp + cin_temp;

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);  
  
  wire [15:0] sum;
  wire cout;
  
  wire [15:0] in1;
  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;
  
  assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
  assign cout = (in1[15] == in2[15] && in1[15] == cin)? 1'b1 : 1'b0;
  
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    assign {cout, sum} = in1_temp + in2_temp + cin_temp;

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum1[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum1[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum1[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
    full_adder_16 FA4(sum1[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
    full_adder_16 FA5(sum1[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
    full_adder_16 FA6(sum1[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
    full_adder_16 FA7(sum1[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
    full_adder_16 FA8(sum1[7], c8, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
    full_adder_16 FA9(sum1[8], c9, in1[8], in2[8], c8);
    full_adder_16 FA10(sum1[9], c10, in1[9], in2[9], c9);
    full_adder_16 FA11(sum1[10], c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
    full_adder_16 FA12(sum1[11], c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);
    full_adder_16 FA13(sum1[12], c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);
    full_adder_16 FA14(sum1[13], c14, in1[13], in2[13], c13);
    full_adder_16 FA15(sum1[14], c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
    full_adder_16 FA16(sum1[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);
endmodule

                      input [15:0] in1, in2,

    full_adder_16 FA16(sum1[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum1, c1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(sum2, c2, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA3(sum3, c3, in1, in2);
    
    assign sum = sum1 ^ sum2 ^ sum3;
    assign cout = c1 ^ c2 ^ c3;
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum1[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum1[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum1[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
    full_adder_16 FA4(sum1[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
    full_adder_16 FA5(sum1[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
    full_adder_16 FA6(sum1[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
    full_adder_16 FA7(sum1[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);

    full_adder_16 FA9(sum1[8], c9, in1[8], in2[8], c8);
    full_adder_16 FA10(sum1[9], c10, in1[9], in2[9], c9);
    full_adder_16 FA11(sum1[10], c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
    full_adder_16 FA12(sum1[11], c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);
    full_adder_16 FA13(sum1[12], c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);
    full_adder_16 FA14(sum1[13], c14, in1[13], in2[13], c13);
    full_adder_16 FA15(sum1[14], c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
    full_adder_16 FA16(sum1[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);
endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum1, c1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(sum2, c2, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA3(sum3, c3, in1, in2);
    
    assign sum = sum1 ^ sum2 ^ sum3;
    assign cout = c1 ^ c2 ^ c3;
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);

    assign sum = in1 ^ in2;
    assign cout = in1 & in2;
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);                      
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
    full_adder_16 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
    full_adder_16 FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
    full_adder_16 FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
    full_adder_16 FA7(sum[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
    full_adder_16 FA8(sum[7], c8, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
    full_adder_16 FA9(sum[8], c9, in1[8], in2[8], c8);
    full_adder_16 FA10(sum[9], c10, in1[9], in2[9], c9);
    full_adder_16 FA11(sum[10], c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
    full_adder_16 FA12(sum[11], c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);
    full_adder_16 FA13(sum[12], c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);
    full_adder_16 FA14(sum[13], c14, in1[13], in2[13], c13);
    full_adder_16 FA15(sum[14], c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
    full_adder_16 FA16(sum[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;

    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

    full_adder_16 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
    full_adder_16 FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);

    full_adder_16 FA16(sum[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);
endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);        
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
      wire [15:0] sum;
      wire cout;
      wire [15:0] in1;
      wire [15:0] in2;
      wire cin;
      
      adder_16_bit_bitwise a1(sum[15:0], cout, in1[15:0], in2[15:0], cin);

module adder_16_bit_bitwise(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
      wire [15:0] sum;
      wire cout;
      wire [15:0] in1;
      wire [15:0] in2;
      wire cin;
      
      wire [15:0] in1_bitwise;
      wire [15:0] in2_bitwise;
      wire cin_bitwise;
      
      assign in1_bitwise = {in1[15:0], in1[15:0]};
      assign in2_bitwise = {in2[15:0], in2[15:0]};

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);  
  
  wire [15:0] sum;
  wire cout;
  
  wire [15:0] in1;
  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;
  
  assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
  assign cout = (in1[15] == in2[15] && in1[15] == cin)? 1'b1 : 1'b0;
  
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);                      
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;

    full_adder_16 FA15(sum[14], c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
    full_adder_16 FA16(sum[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);
endmodule

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.

                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);    

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = {1'b0, in1[15:1]};
    assign in2_temp = {1'b0, in2[15:1]};
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    adder_16_bit adder_16_bit_inst(sum_temp[16:1], cout_temp, in1_temp, in2_temp, cin_temp);

endmodule
Path:  output_files/1550890_adder_16/1550890_simulation
Verilog compilation failed, error:  2

//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);    

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = {1'b0, in1[15:1]};
    assign in2_temp = {1'b0, in2[15:1]};
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    adder_16_bit adder_16_bit_inst(sum_temp[16:1], cout_temp, in1_temp, in2_temp, cin_temp);

endmodule

                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = {1'b0, in1[15:1]};
    assign in2_temp = {1'b0, in2[15:1]};
    assign cin_temp = cin;

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);  
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,

    wire [15:0] in1;

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire temp1;
    wire temp2;
    wire temp3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum, temp1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(temp2, cout, temp1, cin);
    half_adder HA3(temp3, cout, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum, cout, temp2, temp3);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.

                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);                      
  wire [15:0] sum;
  wire cout;
  wire [15:0] in1;
  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;
  
  adder_16_bit a1(sum[15:0], cout, in1[15:0], in2[15:0], cin);
  adder_16_bit a2(sum[31:16], cout, in1[31:16], in2[31:16], cout);

module adder_16_bit(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
  wire [15:0] in1;
  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;
  
  wire [15:0] sum;
  wire cout;
  
  assign sum = in1 + in2;
  assign cout = cin;
endmodule

                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;

  wire cout;

  assign cout = cin;

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    assign {cout, sum} = in1_temp + in2_temp + cin_temp;

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire [15:0] sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum1[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum1[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum1[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
    full_adder_16 FA4(sum1[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
    full_adder_16 FA5(sum1[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
    full_adder_16 FA6(sum1[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);
    full_adder_16 FA7(sum1[6], c7, in1[6], in2[6], c6);
    full_adder_16 FA8(sum1[7], c8, in1[7], in2[7], c7);
    full_adder_16 FA9(sum1[8], c9, in1[8], in2[8], c8);
    full_adder_16 FA10(sum1[9], c10, in1[9], in2[9], c9);
    full_adder_16 FA11(sum1[10], c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
    full_adder_16 FA12(sum1[11], c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);
    full_adder_16 FA13(sum1[12], c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);

    wire c1, c2, c3;
    wire sum1, sum2, sum3;
    
    half_adder HA1(sum1, c1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(sum2, c2, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA3(sum3, c3, in1, in2);
    
    assign sum = sum1 ^ sum2 ^ sum3;
    assign cout = c1 ^ c2 ^ c3;
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);

    assign sum = in1 ^ in2;
    assign cout = in1 & in2;
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

wire [15:0] sum_temp;
wire [15:0] in1_temp;
wire [15:0] in2_temp;

assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
assign in1_temp = in1;
assign in2_temp = in2;

assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
assign cout = sum_temp[16];

endmodule

module adder_1(output sum,
                      output cout,
                      input in1, in2, cin);
   wire c1, c2;
   wire sum;
   
   xor(sum, in1, in2, cin);
   and(c1, in1, in2);
   and(c2, in1, cin);
   and(cout, in2, cin);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
	wire [15:0] sum;
	wire cout;
	wire [15:0] in1;
	wire [15:0] in2;
	wire cin;
	
	assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
	assign cout = (in1[15] == in2[15] && in1[15] == cin)? 1'b1 : 1'b0;
	
endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);

wire xor1, and1, and2;

xor(xor1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, xor1, cin);
and(and1, xor1, cin);
and(and2, in1, in2);
or(cout, and1, and2);

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

wire [15:0] sum_temp;
wire [15:0] in1_temp;
wire [15:0] in2_temp;

assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
assign in1_temp = in1;
assign in2_temp = in2;

assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
assign cout = sum_temp[16];

endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
                          
  wire [15:0] sum;
  wire cout;
  wire [15:0] in1;
  wire [15:0] in2;
  wire cin;
  
  assign sum = in1 + in2 + cin;
  assign cout = (in1[15] == in2[15] && in1[15] == cin)? 1'b1 : 1'b0;
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);
    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;
    
    full_adder_16 FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
    full_adder_16 FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
    full_adder_16 FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);

module full_adder_16(output wire sum,
                      output wire cout,
                      input wire in1, in2,
                      input wire cin);
    wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15;
    half_adder HA1(sum[0], c1, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA2(sum[1], c2, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA3(sum[2], c3, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA4(sum[3], c4, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA5(sum[4], c5, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA6(sum[5], c6, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA7(sum[6], c7, in1, in2);

    half_adder HA13(sum[12], c13, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA14(sum[13], c14, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA15(sum[14], c15, in1, in2);
    half_adder HA16(cout, c15, in1, in2);
endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);
    xor(sum, in1, in2);
    and(cout, in1, in2);
endmodule

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = in1;
    assign in2_temp = in2;
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    assign {cout, sum} = in1_temp + in2_temp + cin_temp;

endmodule

//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.

                      output cout,

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);  

    wire [15:0] sum;
    wire cout;
    wire [15:0] in1;
    wire [15:0] in2;
    wire cin;

    wire [15:0] sum_temp;
    wire cout_temp;
    wire [15:0] in1_temp;
    wire [15:0] in2_temp;
    wire cin_temp;

    assign sum_temp = in1 + in2;
    assign cout_temp = cin + (in1 & in2);

    assign sum = sum_temp[15:0];
    assign cout = cout_temp;

    assign in1_temp = {1'b0, in1[15:1]};
    assign in2_temp = {1'b0, in2[15:1]};
    assign cin_temp = cin;

    adder_16_bit adder_16_bit_inst(sum_temp[16:1], cout_temp, in1_temp, in2_temp, cin_temp);

endmodule

//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.

                      output cout,

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
full_adder FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);

full_adder FA12(sum[11], c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);

full_adder FA14(sum[13], c14, in1[13], in2[13], c13);

//Design a 16-bit adder.
//There are two 16 bit inputs (in1 and in2) and a single carry-in input bit, cin.
//The outputs are a 16 bit value, [15:0] sum, and a single carry-out output bit, cout.
//The module should utilize the inputs (in1 and in2) and the cin bit to obtain the output sum and cout values.
module adder_16(output [15:0] sum,
                      output cout,
                      input [15:0] in1, in2,
                      input cin);

wire c1, c2, c3, c4, c5, c6, c7, c8, c9, c10, c11, c12, c13, c14, c15;

full_adder FA1(sum[0], c1, in1[0], in2[0], cin);
full_adder FA2(sum[1], c2, in1[1], in2[1], c1);
full_adder FA3(sum[2], c3, in1[2], in2[2], c2);
full_adder FA4(sum[3], c4, in1[3], in2[3], c3);
full_adder FA5(sum[4], c5, in1[4], in2[4], c4);
full_adder FA6(sum[5], c6, in1[5], in2[5], c5);

full_adder FA10(sum[9], c10, in1[9], in2[9], c9);
full_adder FA11(sum[10], c11, in1[10], in2[10], c10);
full_adder FA12(sum[11], c12, in1[11], in2[11], c11);
full_adder FA13(sum[12], c13, in1[12], in2[12], c12);
full_adder FA14(sum[13], c14, in1[13], in2[13], c13);
full_adder FA15(sum[14], c15, in1[14], in2[14], c14);
full_adder FA16(sum[15], cout, in1[15], in2[15], c15);

endmodule

module full_adder(output sum,
                  output cout,
                  input in1,
                  input in2,
                  input cin);

wire xor1, and1, and2;

xor(xor1, in1, in2);
xor(sum, xor1, cin);
and(and1, xor1, cin);
and(and2, in1, in2);
or(cout, and1, and2);

endmodule

module half_adder(output wire sum,
                  output wire cout,
                  input wire in1, in2);

xor(sum, in1, in2);
and(cout, in1, in2);

endmodule
